The paper discusses privacy protection in RFID systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes protocols for efficient and fine-grained management of access permissions to tags, which involves cryptography and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the recovery from stolen readers, which is related to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a model for access control, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
